15/08/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- EU Special Representative to Macedonia Michael Sahlin and US Ambassador Lawrence Butler issued a joint statement Friday (13 August) praising Macedonia's progress in establishing a multiethnic state. They also commended the country's Euro-Atlantic integration efforts. The statement was released on the third anniversary of the signing of the Ohrid Framework Agreement. The two officials also welcomed the recent passage of the territorial division law, and urged the adoption of further decentralisation-related bills. (MIA - 13/08/04) 
